    {
      "id": "ODgx-g1tkBNUtOmyC4krK",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -109.4296875,
      "y": 944.78125,
      "width": 907.5865478515625,
      "height": 200,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 80,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "ad",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1008162123,
      "version": 570,
      "versionNonce": 1712996101,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1782042636024,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "In this pattern, we're told to make another Null-Object concrete class, which will either keep\nimplementations empty or have some default values.\n\n- in client's function() will utilize an instance of AbstractClass ac\n- if we didn't utilized Null-Object pattern, then we would have to check on Client\nconditionally using if-else that whether `ac` is initialized or not\n- but with Null-Object pattern we don't need to check as the `ac` would contain reference\nof NullObject",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "In this pattern, we're told to make another Null-Object concrete class, which will either keep implementations empty or have some default values.\n\n- in client's function() will utilize an instance of AbstractClass ac\n- if we didn't utilized Null-Object pattern, then we would have to check on Client conditionally using if-else that whether `ac` is initialized or not\n- but with Null-Object pattern we don't need to check as the `ac` would contain reference of NullObject",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
